The paper discusses the use of Massive MIMO technology for drone communications, which involves aspects of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the need for 3D connectivity and support for fast-moving drones, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for spatially multiplexing entire swarms of drones, which could involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for coordination and control.
